2 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Government evidence DATA and impact commission. (1) There is a
3 government evidence DATA and impact commission.
4 (2) (a) The commission consists of the following voting members:
5 (i) the presiding officer of the senate finance and claims committee or the officer's designee;
6 (ii) the presiding officer of the house appropriations committee or the officer's designee;
7 (iii) the majority presiding officer and the minority vice presiding officer of the legislative audit
8 committee or their designees;
9 (iv) a member of the modernization and risk analysis committee appointed by the presiding officer
10 of the legislative finance committee;
11 (v) a member of the legislature appointed by the governor who is from the opposite party of the
12 member from the modernization and risk analysis committee;
13 (vi) the budget director OR THE DIRECTOR’S DESIGNEE;
14 (vii) the director of the department of administration OR THE DIRECTOR’S DESIGNEE;
15 (viii) the director of the office of state public defender OR THE DIRECTOR’S DESIGNEE;
16 (ix) two directors of a state agency appointed by the governor or their designees; and
17 (x) one member of the public appointed by the governor.
18 (b) The commission consists of the following ex officio, nonvoting members:
19 (i) the legislative fiscal analyst;
20 (ii) the legislative auditor:
21 (iii) a staff member from the legislative services division's legal services office;
22 (iv) a deputy budget director; and
23 (v) the chief data officer.
24 (3) Appointed members of the commission must be compensated and receive travel expenses as
25 provided for in 2-15-124 for each day in attendance at commission meetings or in the performance of any duty
26 or service as a commission member.
27 (4) (a) The department of administration shall staff the commission and pay for the operational
28 costs of the commission.
