12 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Purpose. (1) The commission is charged with developing a system of
13 evidence and impact analysis and with mak ing recommendations for the implementation of the analysis on
14 executive and legislative decisionmaking AND RECOMMENDING A SYSTEM FOR THE COLLECTION AND INTEGRATION OF
15 TARGETED DATA FOR USE BY THE LEGISLATURE AND THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH IN ANALYZING OUTCOMES OF THE AGENCY
16 PROGRAMS, EFFECTIVE USE OF STATE RESOURCES, AND EFFICIENT ADMINISTRATION OF STATE GOVERNMENT.
17 (2) The system developed must allow policymakers to identify inefficient, redundant, and
18 antiquated programs in state government. A report of an evidence and impact analysis conducted using the
19 developed system may include recommendations for improvements in the analyzed programs.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Duties. The commission must receive reports, including but not limited to
22 reports on the following:
23 (1) successful data system implementations that demonstrate existing capabilities to maximize the
24 efficient use of data to inform decisionmaking;
25 (2) examples of programs for which an evidence A DATA and impact analysis is most likely to
26 produce efficiencies, cost savings, or more informed decisionmaking;
27 (3) a review of laws governing the administration of state government and of how to make the
28 operation of state government efficient and transparent;
